## Mixed Exercises

The mixed exercises section provides practice with all skills from the lesson. Problems include:

* Simplifying various radical expressions with different indices.
* Rationalizing denominators with single and binomial radical expressions.
* Finding side length of a cube with the same volume as a rectangular prism.
* Music problem about frequency ratios with √[12]{2}.
* Physics problem simplifying √(t/u) for wave speed.
* Light intensity problem finding d₂/d₁ given I₁ = 50 and I₂ = 24.
* Racing problem comparing times and speeds of two runners.
* Comparing side length ratios of cubes given volumes or surface areas.
* Regularity problem generalizing √x(√x + √(4x) + ... + √(n²x)).
* Modeling trapezoid area to find height.
* Constructing arguments about spherical paperweight packaging.
* Finding combinations of whole numbers for which √[a]{256} = b.
* Proving that (−1 − i√3)/2 is a cube root of 1.
* Explaining why absolute values may be unnecessary when an nth root of an even power results in an odd power.
* Determining which radical expression doesn't belong.

